2e:Te42,Location: London, UK (Hybrid with travel as required)
Reports to: Head of Growth and Revenue
Employment Type: Full-Time


About LaunchGood
LaunchGood is a global crowdfunding platform that helps Muslims worldwide support great causes and bring good to the world. Having grown exponentially in the UK and across the globe, we’re now seeking a dynamic, driven, and strategic leader to take our regional presence to new heights.

Role Overview
We are seeking an experienced Business Development Regional Lead to head our efforts across Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia Pacific regions, with a strong focus on the UK market. This role combines sales leadership, account management, and strategic growth planning. You’ll manage a dedicated team working directly with charities, masjids, schools and community organisations to help them raise funds effectively using LaunchGood's innovative tools and features.As a key regional leader, you’ll drive revenue growth, manage high-impact relationships, and ensure the success of our campaign creators while helping scale the platform’s presence throughout the region

Key Responsibilities

1. Strategic &amp; Sales Leadership
    Own and deliver a growth strategy across the EMEA and APAC region with a focus on high-performing UK operations and growth regions
    Manage sales targets for your region and drive successful outcomes against key performance indicators
    Scout and nurture new leads, organisations, and stakeholders to drive platform usage

2. Client &amp; Campaign Management
    Onboard and support new and existing accounts, helping charities and organisations plan and launch successful campaigns
    Train and coach fundraisers with a consultative, goal-oriented approach
    Build long-term relationships with high-value stakeholders, offering continued support and insights

3. Team Leadership &amp; Collaboration
    Manage and coach a team of regional account managers to peak performance
    Collaborate closely with internal stakeholders across operations, marketing, product, and customer success
    Attend face-to-face client meetings and regional events to build visibility and engagement


Core Competencies

- Leadership Excellence: Proven track record of managing teams and motivating individuals toward target achievement
- Sales &amp; Account Management: Experience in both acquiring new clients and nurturing long-term accounts
- Analytical &amp; Strategic Thinking: Able to craft and execute growth strategies, backed by data
- Communication Mastery: Strong verbal, written, and presentation skills with an ability to influence at all levels
- Process-Oriented: Detail-focused and able to improve systems and workflows
- Ethical &amp; Professional: High standards in personal and professional conduct
- Collaborative Mindset: Skilled at working cross-functionally with diverse, global teams

Qualifications

    - 3+ years in sales, business development, or account management roles, preferably in the nonprofit or tech sectors
    - Previous experience leading regional teams and executing growth strategies
    - Understanding of the UK charity landscape and the fundraising ecosystem is a strong plus
    - Ability to travel across the UK, EMEA, and APAC as needed

Why Join LaunchGood?

    1. Mission-driven work that directly impacts communities around the world
    2. Fast-growing, agile environment with opportunities to lead and innovate
    3. Work with a global team passionate about good causes and Islamic values
    4. Flexible remote work setup with supportive leadership and team culture23:["$","$L11","13",{"animation":"fade-up","delay":80,"children":["$","$L21",null,{"job":{"id":13,"employer_id":77,"external_employer_name":null,"external_employer_website":null,"external_employer_email":null,"employer_package_id":null,"category_id":null,"title":"Business Development Regional Lead – Europe, Middle East, Africa, & Asia Pacific","slug":"launchgood-full-time-2-business-development-regional-lead-europe-middle-east-africa-asia-pacific","description":"$2e","job_type":"Full Time","location":null,"country":null,"salary_min":null,"salary_max":null,"salary_currency":"USD","salary_type":"yearly","experience_level":null,"career_level":null,"apply_type":"platform","apply_url":null,"is_featured":true,"is_urgent":true,"status":"active","expires_at":"2026-05-17T00:00:00.000000Z","views_count":409,"created_at":"2026-03-18T15:13:47.000000Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T12:29:13.000000Z","is_external":false,"employer":{"id":77,"company_name":"LaunchGood","slug":"launchgood","logo_path":"logos/pOna5UOHobKzv9artMEUDqsAW3kI5uQ1OqxsH6N1.png"},"category":null},"variant":"list"}]}]
2f:T115b,Position Overview

We are seeking a visionary Head of Growth &amp; Revenue to spearhead LaunchGood's next phase of exponential expansion through a combination of product, process and people, as the world's leading crowdfunding platform for Muslims.

We’re looking for an experienced leader who can help us scale our impact across global Muslim communities through growth strategies and innovative product that drives sustainable revenue acceleration, market expansion, and donor acquisition at a large scale.

This senior leadership position sits at the intersection of strategy and execution, responsible for orchestrating multi-channel growth ecosystems while building high-performing teams that consistently deliver breakthrough results for causes that matter most to our communities.

The successful candidate will be instrumental in positioning LaunchGood as the Go-to Sadaqah platform, while scaling operations to support our ambitious mission of empowering good worldwide.

Here are some things our past Head of Growth worked on:

   1. Reorganizing Business Development and other teams into a “Customer Success” team
   2. Identifying a fast-growing trend in influencer fundraising and building a team, strategies and products around it
   3. Driving fast and effective crisis responses (e.g. Turkey earthquake, Gaza relief) through cross-department collaboration with marketing, product,   business development, etc.
   4. Hosting 40+ influencers in Doha as part of the GMW Summit
   5. Organizing team-wide retreat bringing together team players from across the globe to plan for next phase of growth

What our future Head of Growth might find themselves working on:

    - Building phase one of LaunchGood+ which includes a range of fundraising back-end tools for charities
    - Developing programmes for ambassadors and influencers to further amplify the support the incredible work they are doing
    - Scaling our North America operations

Key Responsibilities:

Leadership &amp; Management
- Lead and manage growth teams consisting of Business Development, Ads, Zakat, Emergency Response, Influencers and Ambassadors
- Shura; Serve as a key member of Shura (extended leadership team), contributing to company-wide strategic decisions that advance our mission
- Collaborate; Foster collaboration and alignment across departments (especially Programs and Product) to deliver alignment and effective high value programs like Ramadan &amp; Dhul Hijjah etc.

Growth Innovation &amp; Muslim Fundraising Market Leadership

- Accelerate the growth of LaunchGood through product, process and people
- Identify new growth opportunities in existing or new verticals
- Lead market expansion into emerging Muslim-majority territories as part of vision to become the go-to sadaqah platform for the Ummah
- Data-informed growth approach where ideas are aggressively tested and lessons learned
- Lead our LaunchGood+ operations, focussing on packaging and go to market strategy
- Collaborate with Product on innovative approaches to giving that bridge traditional philanthropy with modern digital fundraising
- Intentionally engage and build strong relationships with industry leaders as well as our customers, e.g CEO’s and Fundraising Directors

Experience

- 8+ years of progressive leadership experience in growth or business development roles, preferably in tech, fundraising, or Islamic economy sector
- History of managing multi-layer teams and departments (including senior managers and Directors)
- Experience building and scaling relationships, particularly in diverse global cultural contexts

Skills &amp; Competencies

 - Strong strategic thinking and analytical capabilities with cultural sensitivity to Islamic values and practices
 - Excellent relationship-building and partnership development skills within Muslim communities
 - Data-driven approach to decision making with strong analytical skills and understanding of Muslim Fundraising sector
 - Outstanding communication and presentation abilities, with ability to engage diverse global audiences
 - Proven ability to drive results in fast-paced, dynamic environments while maintaining ethical standards
 - Experience with diverse growth channels including digital marketing, partnerships, and community-based outreach
 - Understanding of Islamic principles related to finance, charity, and business practices24:["$","$L11","12",{"animation":"fade-up","delay":160,"children":["$","$L21",null,{"job":{"id":12,"employer_id":77,"external_employer_name":null,"external_employer_website":null,"external_employer_email":null,"employer_package_id":null,"category_id":24,"title":"Head of Growth and Revenue","slug":"adella-berlianti-canada-full-time-2-head-of-growth-and-revenue","description":"$2f","job_type":"Full Time","location":"1378","country":null,"salary_min":null,"salary_max":null,"salary_currency":"USD","salary_type":"yearly","experience_level":null,"career_level":null,"apply_type":"platform","apply_url":"https://secure.collage.co/jobs/launchgood/55921","is_featured":true,"is_urgent":true,"status":"active","expires_at":"2026-05-17T00:00:00.000000Z","views_count":355,"created_at":"2026-03-18T13:00:46.000000Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T12:29:13.000000Z","is_external":false,"employer":{"id":77,"company_name":"LaunchGood","slug":"launchgood","logo_path":"logos/pOna5UOHobKzv9artMEUDqsAW3kI5uQ1OqxsH6N1.png"},"category":{"id":24,"name":"Sales","slug":"sales"}},"variant":"list"}]}]
30:T109a,<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-deeds">About Deeds</h3>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="securing-our-ummah-s-digital-dignity">Securing Our Ummah's Digital Dignity</h3>



<p class="">Deeds is the parent company of The Masjid App. See more at&nbsp;<a href="https://thedeeds.net/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">thedeeds.net</a>.</p>



<p class="">In today's interconnected world, our digital and physical lives are inseparably linked. Companies routinely collect and analyze our personal data, creating&nbsp;real-world consequences&nbsp;for Muslim communities. When your online activities, location data, and communications are tracked, this information can directly impact physical safety, community surveillance, and&nbsp;targeted discrimination&nbsp;against the Ummah. Our privacy solutions&nbsp;protect&nbsp;not just your digital identity, but your actual lived experience—preventing biased algorithms from restricting your opportunities, protecting community spaces from unnecessary monitoring, and ensuring your personal data isn't used to inform policies that harm Muslims worldwide. By&nbsp;securing your digital footprint, you're taking a practical step to protect both yourself and the broader&nbsp;Ummah&nbsp;from very real physical threats that begin in the digital realm.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-the-masjid-app">About The Masjid App</h3>



<p class="">Connecting Muslim communities with their local masjids in a safe and optimized way—like never before</p>



<p class="">Masjids are the data centers of our communities. It is of the utmost importance to help Masjids protect not just their immediate community but preventing their community from being leveraged to power harm to other parts of the Ummah. For too long, Masjids have been using tools not designed for masjids—systems that aren't optimized for their unique needs and often compromise the privacy of their congregations.</p>



<p class="">Unlike big tech's biased algorithms that show communities only what generates themselves money and power, The Masjid App provides real free speech and transparent communication, making events and announcements accessible to all without manipulation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="expo-developer-with-native-ios-android-experience">Expo Developer with Native iOS &amp; Android Experience</h3>



<p class="">We're looking for a developer who has strong native iOS and Android experience and has embraced the Expo ecosystem. Your expertise will help optimize our Expo applications and bridge between native and JavaScript capabilities.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="requirements-responsibilities">Requirements &amp; Responsibilities</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Implement native functionality using Expo Modules API and Config Plugins</li>



<li class="">Optimize app performance using tools from Xcode, Android Studio, and Expo</li>



<li class="">Expert knowledge of Expo SDK, build system, and development lifecycle</li>



<li class="">Deep understanding of iOS widgets, App Clips, Android widgets, and Instant Apps</li>



<li class="">Experience with advanced push notification techniques</li>



<li class="">Strong TypeScript skills (ideally completed totaltypescript.com tutorials)</li>



<li class="">Proficiency with React performance optimization</li>



<li class="">Experience with map implementation nuances</li>



<li class="">Knowledge of virtualization and list optimization techniques</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-makes-you-successful">What Makes You Successful</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Strong foundation in both native mobile development and Expo ecosystem</li>



<li class="">Ability to identify and implement performance optimizations across platforms</li>



<li class="">Knowledge of when to use native solutions vs. JavaScript implementations</li>



<li class="">Commitment to keeping up with advancements in Expo, iOS, Android, and related technologies</li>



<li class="">Experience with full EAS system</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="apply-now">Apply Now</h3>



<p class="">Send your resume and a brief introduction to apply for this position.</p>25:["$","$L11","9",{"animation":"fade-up","delay":240,"children":["$","$L21",null,{"job":{"id":9,"employer_id":21,"external_employer_name":null,"external_employer_website":null,"external_employer_email":null,"employer_package_id":null,"category_id":7,"title":"Senior Mobile Developer","slug":"senior-mobile-developer","description":"$30","job_type":"Remote","location":null,"country":null,"salary_min":null,"salary_max":null,"salary_currency":"USD","salary_type":"yearly","experience_level":null,"career_level":null,"apply_type":"external","apply_url":"https://themasjidapp.org/careers/mobile-developer","is_featured":true,"is_urgent":false,"status":"active","expires_at":null,"views_count":1884,"created_at":"2025-12-01T14:17:59.000000Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T12:29:13.000000Z","is_external":false,"employer":{"id":21,"company_name":"The Masjid App","slug":"the-masjid-app","logo_path":"logos/2Zg31Opq3PAnp42jTzhu16M3KX0G3LoWyPaPSC2X.png"},"category":{"id":7,"name":"Engineering","slug":"engineering"}},"variant":"list"}]}]
31:T19ac,<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-deeds">About Deeds</h3>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="securing-our-ummah-s-digital-dignity">Securing Our Ummah's Digital Dignity</h3>



<p class="">Deeds is the parent company of The Masjid App. See more at&nbsp;<a href="https://thedeeds.net/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">thedeeds.net</a>.</p>



<p class="">In today's interconnected world, our digital and physical lives are inseparably linked. Companies routinely collect and analyze our personal data, creating&nbsp;real-world consequences&nbsp;for Muslim communities. When your online activities, location data, and communications are tracked, this information can directly impact physical safety, community surveillance, and&nbsp;targeted discrimination&nbsp;against the Ummah. Our privacy solutions&nbsp;protect&nbsp;not just your digital identity, but your actual lived experience—preventing biased algorithms from restricting your opportunities, protecting community spaces from unnecessary monitoring, and ensuring your personal data isn't used to inform policies that harm Muslims worldwide. By&nbsp;securing your digital footprint, you're taking a practical step to protect both yourself and the broader&nbsp;Ummah&nbsp;from very real physical threats that begin in the digital realm.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-the-masjid-app">About The Masjid App</h3>



<p class="">Connecting Muslim communities with their local masjids in a safe and optimized way—like never before</p>



<p class="">Masjids are the data centers of our communities. It is of the utmost importance to help Masjids protect not just their immediate community but preventing their community from being leveraged to power harm to other parts of the Ummah. For too long, Masjids have been using tools not designed for masjids—systems that aren't optimized for their unique needs and often compromise the privacy of their congregations.</p>



<p class="">Unlike big tech's biased algorithms that show communities only what generates themselves money and power, The Masjid App provides real free speech and transparent communication, making events and announcements accessible to all without manipulation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-the-role">About The Role</h3>



<p class="">We are seeking a Senior Full Stack Engineer with advanced expertise in Next.js, TypeScript, and cloud infrastructure. You will be responsible for evaluating and potentially implementing Cloudflare architecture solutions to solve our global speed challenges while working with our existing Next.js (Page Router) app. This role requires deep knowledge of distributed PostgreSQL database architecture, experience with Prisma ORM, and SEO expertise. You will build high-performance applications in the frontend while ensuring smooth integration with various services and APIs globally. We use Stripe and will use Twilio/SignalWire. Your help will be needed across the stack, especially in evaluating and comitting to Twilio/SignalWire.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="responsibilities">Responsibilities</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Design and develop full-stack applications using Next.js (Page Router), React, and TypeScript</li>



<li class="">Stay at the cutting edge of technologies used, evaluating new features for potential benefits</li>



<li class="">Familiar with Cloudfalre services including R2 storage, live streaming, images, CDN, KV, and workers.</li>



<li class="">Create robust API routes with proper validation using Zod, with readable and localized error handling</li>



<li class="">Develop advanced SEO strategies including sitemap generation and structured data implementation</li>



<li class="">Familiar with good database design principles and optimization techniques for performance and scalability of the API.</li>



<li class="">Implement robust observability with New Relic for performance monitoring and cost optimization</li>



<li class="">Create and maintain NPM packages for internal code reuse and component libraries</li>



<li class="">Manage deployment pipelines and DevOps tasks in a distributed cloud environment</li>



<li class="">Collaborate with the mobile team to ensure seamless cross-platform data synchronization</li>



<li class="">Optimize applications for performance, scalability, and security</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="requirements">Requirements</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Expert-level TypeScript skills (wizard-level proficiency, ideally having completed all tutorials and workshops from totalTypescript.com)</li>



<li class="">Deep experience with Next.js Page Router architecture and optimization techniques</li>



<li class="">Strong knowledge of Cloudflare's ecosystem including Workers, Pages, R2, Images, and live streaming, and other capabilities</li>



<li class="">Experience with Prisma ORM and its Typescript design</li>



<li class="">Proven experience designing and implementing distributed PostgreSQL databases with horizontal sharding</li>



<li class="">Expert-level SEO knowledge including technical implementation for Next.js applications</li>



<li class="">Experience implementing comprehensive observability solutions with New Relic</li>



<li class="">Strong understanding of edge computing architecture and best practices</li>



<li class="">Experience with Stripe API integration and handling banking/financial transactions</li>



<li class="">Expertise in optimizing application performance at global scale</li>



<li class="">Solid understanding of web security best practices in distributed systems</li>



<li class="">Experience with modern CI/CD workflows and infrastructure as code</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="preferred-qualifications">Preferred Qualifications</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Experience optimizing Prisma for high-performance applications</li>



<li class="">Knowledge of implementing Zod for robust API validation with localized error messages</li>



<li class="">Advanced understanding of databases for global performance</li>



<li class="">Deep understanding of Datadog's APM, RUM, and infrastructure monitoring capabilities</li>



<li class="">Ability to evaluate and implement emerging technologies before they become mainstream in Typescript, Next.js, cloud-services</li>
</ul>



