<p class="">Send your resume and a brief introduction to apply for this position.</p>26:["$","$L11","8",{"animation":"fade-up","delay":320,"children":["$","$L21",null,{"job":{"id":8,"employer_id":21,"external_employer_name":null,"external_employer_website":null,"external_employer_email":null,"employer_package_id":null,"category_id":7,"title":"Senior Full Stack Engineer (Next.js, Vercel & Cloudflare Expert)","slug":"senior-full-stack-engineer-next-js-vercel-cloudflare-expert","description":"$31","job_type":"Remote","location":null,"country":null,"salary_min":null,"salary_max":null,"salary_currency":"USD","salary_type":"yearly","experience_level":null,"career_level":null,"apply_type":"external","apply_url":"https://themasjidapp.org/careers/full-stack-engineer","is_featured":true,"is_urgent":false,"status":"active","expires_at":null,"views_count":1424,"created_at":"2025-12-01T14:14:58.000000Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T12:19:33.000000Z","is_external":false,"employer":{"id":21,"company_name":"The Masjid App","slug":"the-masjid-app","logo_path":"logos/2Zg31Opq3PAnp42jTzhu16M3KX0G3LoWyPaPSC2X.png"},"category":{"id":7,"name":"Engineering","slug":"engineering"}},"variant":"list"}]}]
32:T1650,<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-deeds">About Deeds</h3>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="securing-our-ummah-s-digital-dignity">Securing Our Ummah's Digital Dignity</h3>



<p class="">Deeds is the parent company of The Masjid App. See more at&nbsp;<a href="https://thedeeds.net/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">thedeeds.net</a>.</p>



<p class="">In today's interconnected world, our digital and physical lives are inseparably linked. Companies routinely collect and analyze our personal data, creating&nbsp;real-world consequences&nbsp;for Muslim communities. When your online activities, location data, and communications are tracked, this information can directly impact physical safety, community surveillance, and&nbsp;targeted discrimination&nbsp;against the Ummah. Our privacy solutions&nbsp;protect&nbsp;not just your digital identity, but your actual lived experience—preventing biased algorithms from restricting your opportunities, protecting community spaces from unnecessary monitoring, and ensuring your personal data isn't used to inform policies that harm Muslims worldwide. By&nbsp;securing your digital footprint, you're taking a practical step to protect both yourself and the broader&nbsp;Ummah&nbsp;from very real physical threats that begin in the digital realm.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-the-masjid-app">About The Masjid App</h3>



<p class="">Connecting Muslim communities with their local masjids in a safe and optimized way—like never before</p>



<p class="">Masjids are the data centers of our communities. It is of the utmost importance to help Masjids protect not just their immediate community but preventing their community from being leveraged to power harm to other parts of the Ummah. For too long, Masjids have been using tools not designed for masjids—systems that aren't optimized for their unique needs and often compromise the privacy of their congregations.</p>



<p class="">Unlike big tech's biased algorithms that show communities only what generates themselves money and power, The Masjid App provides real free speech and transparent communication, making events and announcements accessible to all without manipulation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-the-role">About The Role</h3>



<p class="">We're seeking an experienced Senior UI/UX Designer proficient in Figma to lead our multi-platform design strategy. You'll influence our product roadmap while collaborating across all departments, especially with sales and customer engagement teams.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="key-responsibilities">Key Responsibilities</h3>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="product-strategy-design-leadership">Product Strategy &amp; Design Leadership</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Shape product roadmap based on user insights and technical feasibility</li>



<li class="">Assess engineering capabilities to create realistic implementation timelines</li>



<li class="">Manage comprehensive design system in Figma</li>



<li class="">Review all GitHub PRs for design implementation</li>



<li class="">Proactively gather feedback from sales and customer engagement teams</li>



<li class="">Integrate customer insights into design decisions</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="user-understanding-cross-platform-design">User Understanding &amp; Cross-Platform Design</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Design for diverse user personas including masjid goers and administrators</li>



<li class="">Create cohesive experiences across our ecosystem:</li>



<li class="">Mobile app with social features, website widgets, and hosting</li>



<li class="">TV displays (prayer clock, slideshow, fundraiser)</li>



<li class="">Touchscreen kiosks and handheld donation devices</li>



<li class="">Work with engineering to implement tracking for data-driven decisions</li>



<li class="">Design dashboard interfaces for website hosting, DNS management, and domain services</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="qualifications">Qualifications</h3>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="required-experience">Required Experience</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">5+ years UI/UX design experience with multi-platform systems</li>



<li class="">Advanced Figma proficiency</li>



<li class="">High familiarity with Muslim masjid interaction experience</li>



<li class="">Social media design experience for mobile applications</li>



<li class="">Knowledge of website hosting, DNS management, domain purchasing, and domain transferring</li>



<li class="">Experience with product roadmap planning</li>



<li class="">Ability to evaluate engineering feasibility</li>



<li class="">Track record of incorporating customer feedback</li>



<li class="">Experience reviewing code for design implementation</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="bonus-skills">Bonus Skills</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Graphic design capabilities</li>



<li class="">Knowledge of payment systems and donation flows</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-makes-you-successful">What Makes You Successful</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Proactive approach to gathering cross-departmental feedback</li>



<li class="">Strong technical intuition about feasibility and prioritization</li>



<li class="">Ability to balance design ideals with practical implementation</li>



<li class="">Skill in translating user needs into clear design solutions</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="apply-now">Apply Now</h3>



<p class="">Send your resume and a brief introduction to apply for this position.</p>27:["$","$L11","7",{"animation":"fade-up","delay":400,"children":["$","$L21",null,{"job":{"id":7,"employer_id":21,"external_employer_name":null,"external_employer_website":null,"external_employer_email":null,"employer_package_id":null,"category_id":5,"title":"Senior UI/UX Designer","slug":"senior-ui-ux-designer","description":"$32","job_type":"Remote","location":null,"country":null,"salary_min":null,"salary_max":null,"salary_currency":"USD","salary_type":"yearly","experience_level":null,"career_level":null,"apply_type":"external","apply_url":"https://themasjidapp.org/careers/senior-ui-ux-designer","is_featured":true,"is_urgent":false,"status":"active","expires_at":null,"views_count":1823,"created_at":"2025-12-01T13:57:39.000000Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T12:19:33.000000Z","is_external":false,"employer":{"id":21,"company_name":"The Masjid App","slug":"the-masjid-app","logo_path":"logos/2Zg31Opq3PAnp42jTzhu16M3KX0G3LoWyPaPSC2X.png"},"category":{"id":5,"name":"Design","slug":"design"}},"variant":"list"}]}]
33:T11ed,<p class=""><strong>Job Title:</strong> Sous Chef- Halal Specialty <br><strong>Job Location:</strong> Charlotte-USA-28219 <br><strong>Work Location Type:</strong> On-Site <br><strong>Salary Range:</strong> $60,000.00 - 70,000.00</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="about-us"><strong>About us</strong></h2>



<p class="">LSG Sky Chefs is one of the world’s largest airline catering and hospitality providers, known for its outstanding reputation and dynamic approach in the industry. Voted “Airline Caterer of the Year in North America” for 2023 and 2024, we are committed to excellence and innovation, driven by the dedication and expertise of our talented employees. Our team members are the heart and soul of our success, consistently delivering exceptional culinary experiences and outstanding service to our clients and their passengers across North and Latin America.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="role-purpose-statement"><strong>Role Purpose Statement</strong></h2>



<p class="">The Specialty Sous Chef (Halal) supports the Executive Chef in producing high-quality halal-compliant meals for airline passengers. This role ensures strict adherence to halal standards, food safety regulations, and airline catering specifications while managing kitchen operations and staff.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="main-accountabilities"><strong>Main Accountabilities</strong></h2>



<p class=""><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Halal Menu Development: Collaborate with the Executive Chef to design and update halal-compliant menus tailored for airline passengers, considering cultural preferences and flight duration.</li>



<li class="">Meal Preparation: Oversee preparation and cooking of halal dishes in compliance with airline catering standards and halal certification requirements.</li>



<li class="">Compliance &amp; Documentation: Ensure all ingredients, suppliers, and processes meet halal certification and airline regulatory standards. Maintain accurate documentation for audits.</li>



<li class="">Production Efficiency: Manage large-scale meal production for multiple flights while maintaining quality, consistency, and timely delivery.</li>



<li class="">Inventory &amp; Procurement: Monitor stock levels, order halal-certified ingredients, and minimize waste in a high-volume environment.</li>



<li class="">Team Leadership: Train and supervise kitchen staff on halal preparation techniques, portion control, and airline-specific packaging requirements.</li>



<li class="">Quality Assurance: Conduct regular checks for hygiene, food safety, and halal compliance throughout the kitchen and production line.</li>



<li class="">Customer Satisfaction: Address special dietary requests and ensure meals meet airline and passenger expectations.</li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>Leadership</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Ensure that the area of responsibility is properly organized, staffed and directed</li>



<li class="">Guide, motivate and develop the subordinate employees within the Human Resources Policy</li>



<li class="">Make the company's values and management principles live in the department(s)</li>



<li class="">Implement and control the cost budget in the area of responsibility; initiate and steer corrective actions in case of deviations</li>



<li class="">Participate and support company sponsored initiatives such as Global Quality Standard (GQS), HACCP, Lean Manufacturing <br> </li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="knowledge-skills-and-experience"><strong>Knowledge, Skills and Experience</strong></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Culinary degree or equivalent professional experience.</li>



<li class="">Minimum 3 years of experience in airline catering or high-volume food production, with expertise in halal cuisine.</li>



<li class="">Strong knowledge of halal certification standards and airline catering regulations.</li>



<li class="">Leadership and team management skills.</li>



<li class="">Ability to work in a fast-paced, high-pressure environment with tight deadlines.</li>



<li class="">Excellent communication and organizational skills.</li>



<li class=""><strong>Arabic speaking preferred</strong> (to communicate effectively with suppliers, clients, or team members when needed).</li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>LSG Sky Chefs</strong>&nbsp;is an EEO and Affirmative Action Employer of Women/Minorities/Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities.</p>



