34:Td56,<div>
<p class=""><strong>Positions:</strong></p>
</div>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Marketing Intern</li>



<li class="">This is a hybrid non-paid internship position for academic credit.<br></li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Basic understanding of Zoom</li>



<li class="">Strong writing skills</li>



<li class="">Familiarity with social media platforms: LinkedIn, Facebook, and Instagram</li>



<li class="">Age Requirement: 18 or older</li>



<li class="">Must be in college majoring in public relations/business/journalism or a related field.</li>



<li class="">A passion to learn and contribute!<br></li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>Preferred:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Experience with Canva</li>



<li class="">Experience with Social Media Platforms (Ex: Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn, etc.)</li>



<li class="">Experience with website editing<br></li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>Internship training will include:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Virtual Marketing Techniques &amp; Online Meeting Skills</li>



<li class="">Interfacing with board members, executive leadership, administrators, and businesses</li>



<li class="">Social Media Platforms: LinkedIn, Facebook, and Instagram</li>



<li class="">Content Creation using Adobe, Photoshop, or Canva<br></li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>Role &amp; Responsibilities:<br></strong><br>After the initial training on our organization and its programs, interns will work on providing and creating information regarding our programs. The intern will work with our staff to raise our organization's brand profile and increase public engagement.<br></p>



<p class=""><strong>Responsibilities can include:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Create engaging content, presentations, press releases, website content, etc.</li>



<li class="">Meet with staff to coordinate and manage our events, tools, and brand.</li>



<li class="">Attend meetings with staff on a weekly basis.</li>



<li class="">Posting daily content to social media platforms.</li>



<li class="">Researching tips and information regarding the Muslim community</li>



<li class="">Manage any communications requests and direct messaging.</li>



<li class="">Collaborate with other staff and interns to make sure we are staying on brand in presenting our organization's goals and values.</li>
</ul>



<p class=""><em><strong>Schedules are flexible. All meetings and tasks will be done remotely or in-person by the intern. Access to a laptop/computer with video and reliable internet is required to complete internship tasks.</strong></em><br></p>



<p class=""><strong><a href="https://forms.gle/HLFpYtytb13WJ2ta6">CLICK HERE,</a>&nbsp;TO SUBMIT YOUR APPLICATION:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li class="">Submit your resumes with your portfolio link of work samples</li>



<li class="">Additionally, you can send your application to: marketing@icoi.net</li>
</ul>



<p class=""><strong>Deadline for Application: January 25, 2026<br></strong><br><strong>About the Islamic Center of Irvine<br></strong>Founded in 2004, the Islamic Center of Irvine (ICOI), is a 501(c)3 nonprofit organization that provides religious education, spiritual support and social services.</p>



